==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[γεωμετρία]]''' (''geometria'') "geometry, land-survey", from '''[[γεωμετρέω]]''' (''geometreo'') "to practise or to profess geometry, to measure, to survey land", from '''[[γαία]]''' (''gaea'') "earth, land, country" + '''[[μετρέω]]''' (''metreo'') "to measure, to count".

===Noun===
'''geometry'''
#The branch of [[mathematics]] dealing with spatial relationships.
#An item's relative spatial attributes


